I’ve had years before that took so much from me but 2022 felt like a year of nothing but the highest of moments. It felt like God said you’ve had enough lows now it’s time for some highs. I can not post this as if every single day was the best day ever because it was hardly that, but I can say I’m immensely grateful… for the laughs, the hugs, the love, the support, the work, the struggle, the FOOOOOD, the drinks, the dancing, the trips! The time spent being good to the people around me and them being good to me! I’m welcoming 2023 but it better not come in with that bullshit and I mean it.  I have one more recap to post of last year. It just wouldn’t be right not to have my friends and family in one. ❤️

Healing is such a beautiful thing. 
Valentine’s Day has always been a bitter holiday for me. I’ll Walk into a store ready to knock all that bullshit over. Years of abstaining and dating with a purpose I can say I’m ALMOST ready again 😬. Love is scary at times. The vulnerability of it especially after a heart break could seem impossible to do again m. 7 years of Muvahood with the sweetest girl I know. 💓 
Idc what anyone says motherhood is the hardest hood I’ve ever had to go through. The initiation process is brutal. They dnt just jump you in you actually have to give birth to be in it. Although many women don’t survive child birth you still aren’t even considered a mom unless you actively are responsible for this being every single day of their life. To knowingly accept that responsibility without having control of the world around them or their very own thoughts, feelings and actions is INSANE! Yet we do it everyday WITH COMPLAINTS, at least on my end, but without any doubt that i will get up everyday and be responsible for this being I brought into this world. Praying that she gives the world all that she gives me. That’s when you know you’re raising a person right. Happy Mother’s Day to the mothers that make it their responsibility to bring to this world something… someone…. Good! ❤️

My 2023 in no particular order was filled with so many high moments the low ones had no chance.  I saw 3 different countries. I took my daughter to Disney. I fell in love 🥰. I rode a horse and a camel 😂. I swam in the ocean too many times to count. I stood at the top of tallest building in the world. No way in January of last year did I think any of this would happen and I’m so grateful and blessed to have made it through last year with all my family and friends still here. A happy and healthy child. My career intact and growing with so much hope for 2024.
